This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama in 2010, declaring January 16th as Religious Freedom Day. It highlights the importance of religious freedom in the United States and commemorates the Virginia Statute for Religious Freedom, which was a statement of principle declaring freedom of religion as a natural right for all humanity. The proclamation emphasizes the commitment of the United States to advocate for religious freedom worldwide and opposes any restrictions on religious expression. It calls on all Americans to commemorate this day and engage in activities that promote and protect religious freedom for future generations.